+    "operator_design_decisions": "The operator directed 'Approved, please proceed' for the FULL bundle after being offered scope-down/pause alternatives, and pre-approved two lighter mechanisms over the feature_list's aspirational phrasing: (017) a PLUGGABLE caller-supplied --ci-run-file (deterministic, offline), NOT a live GitHub Actions API call inside the tool -- the tool stays a deterministic collector and the orchestrator/caller (which already resolves CI runs) supplies the reference; (018.1) an ADDITIVE --tolerate-untracked-prefix option, NOT a scratch-checkout/clean-worktree isolation mode -- it achieves 018(1)'s stated goal (a feature's own in-flight .agent artifacts need not be enumerated file-by-file) with far less risk to the load-bearing 043/044 exact-match dir-collapse semantics. The feature_list 056 acceptance_tests (discriminating test per item; 043/044 preserved; sweeps+e2e green; five exit codes unchanged) are met by these mechanisms.",
+    "preservation_note": "The committed 043/044 approved-exception semantics are load-bearing and preserved: git collapses an entirely-untracked directory to one trailing-slash porcelain entry, and the exact --tolerate-untracked matches that collapsed 'dir/' entry unchanged (E06-b). -z does NOT imply --untracked-files=all, so the collapse is retained (021.1). The exact-match set keeps the historic declared_tolerated_untracked kind; the prefix set uses declared_tolerated_untracked_prefix, so the two are never conflated.",
